<!-- 2 SUMMARY -->
<section id="summary" class="sec">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="reveal">
      <div class="sec-label">Summary</div>
      <h2 class="sec-title">Four core contributions.</h2>
      <p class="sec-sub">This study identifies, quantifies, and mitigates semantic leakage in speech-based depression detection through a comprehensive cue-aware framework.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="g2 stagger mt36">
      <div class="s-card reveal">
        <span class="s-card-num">01</span>
        <h4>Semantic Leakage Hypothesis</h4>
        <p>We identify lexically explicit depression-related cue spans in interview speech as a major, previously under-audited confound. Models trained on "acoustic-only" inputs can still exploit semantic content embedded in the speech signal.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="s-card reveal">
        <span class="s-card-num">02</span>
        <h4>Cue-Aware Agent</h4>
        <p>We develop an Agent integrating multiple ASR systems and LLM-based cue extraction to produce robust transcripts, cue spans with timestamps, and derived Cue-Excluded / Cue-Only audio for controlled evaluation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="s-card reveal">
        <span class="s-card-num">03</span>
        <h4>CueGate Module</h4>
        <p>We propose a lightweight, two-stream, sparsely gated model with Top-K selection and contrastive learning to enable accurate and efficient cue detection on new datasets without requiring transcripts at inference.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="s-card reveal">
        <span class="s-card-num">04</span>
        <h4>DepCue Corpus</h4>
        <p>We contribute ManDIC, a new Chinese clinical interview corpus of 557 recordings with HAMD-17 annotations, to mitigate the lack of Mandarin resources for cue-aware depression modeling.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

