<!-- 8 GLOSSARY -->
<section id="glossary" class="sec">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="reveal">
      <div class="sec-label">Glossary</div>
      <h2 class="sec-title">Key terms explained.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="gloss-grid stagger mt36">
      <div class="gloss-item reveal">
        <div class="gloss-term">Semantic Leakage</div>
        <p>The phenomenon where models trained on audio inputs exploit lexically explicit depression-related content embedded in speech signals, rather than learning generalizable acoustic-prosodic patterns.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="gloss-item reveal">
        <div class="gloss-term">Cue</div>
        <p>Lexically explicit, depression-related expressions (e.g., "I feel hopeless") whose acoustic spans are highly predictive of depression labels in interview corpora.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="gloss-item reveal">
        <div class="gloss-term">Cue-Aware Agent</div>
        <p>An automated pipeline combining ASR systems and LLM-based parsing to detect depression-related cues and map them to waveform timestamps for controlled audio reconstruction.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="gloss-item reveal">
        <div class="gloss-term">CueGate</div>
        <p>A lightweight neural module for acoustic cue span detection, featuring two-stream architecture, sparse gating with Top-K selection, and contrastive learning for handling class imbalance.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="gloss-item reveal">
        <div class="gloss-term">Cue-Excluded Audio</div>
        <p>Audio reconstructed by removing detected cue spans from the original recording, enabling controlled evaluation of model dependence on semantic content.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

